# Project Standards & Philosophy

## Core Principles
- **Content-first**: Prioritize content and typography over decorative elements.
- **Fast & SEO-friendly**: Use Server Components by default. Keep the JS bundle minimal.
- **Accessible**: Ensure high contrast, proper semantic HTML, and ARIA labels where needed.
- **Minimalist**: Clean typography, consistent spacing, no fancy animations.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 15 (App Router)
- **Language**: TypeScript (Strict mode)
- **React**: version 19
- **Content**: MDX with frontmatter (gray-matter)
- **Styling**: Global CSS (minimalist)

## Code Standards
- Use functional components and modern React patterns.
- Prefer Server Components unless client-side interactivity is absolutely required.
- Maintain consistent spacing using CSS variables defined in `styles/globals.css`.
- All text should be easily crawlable by search engines.
